    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on several favorable matchups today, with **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) headlining our lineup as the only players to eclipse the 80-point threshold. **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a massive 14% park boost and a soft matchup against Jose Quintana, whose xERA of 5.04 is the highest on our board. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an offensive environment, with a rare 5% wind-out factor and a strong platoon advantage against Seth Lugo. While the elite hold potential of Lugo suppresses his overall score slightly, **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start in a prime #2 hole. **Andy Pages** also makes for a high-upside play at 74.43, mirroring the same park and platoon environment that elevates **Kyle Tucker**.\n\nStrategic rotation is key today, as **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (67.85) provide excellent value against weak arms like Jake Irvin and Bryce Elder. We have opted to bench **Coby Mayo** (50.81), who was the final omission from our starting nine. While **Coby Mayo** possesses intriguing power, his negative platoon split against Seth Lugo and the resulting optimizer downgrade against a high-efficiency reliever caused him to fall behind the reliable efficiency of **Brady House** (60.72). It is worth noting that **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (55.26) and **Josh Lowe** (53.53) are facing tougher assignments against Reid Detmers and Dylan Cease, respectively; while their projections are lower, their pedigree keeps them firmly in the starting rotation. Managers should stay alert to final lineup confirmations, as the status of **Liam Hicks** (52.87) and **Nasim Nunez** (55.14) is currently reliant on projected batting order; any move down the lineup for these lower-tier options could push them below the 40-point floor and necessitate a swap for available depth.",
